findings.recommendation:
Validate the incoming payload with a strict schema before using it. Use zod or a manual allow-list:
  const ALLOWED_TYPES = new Set(['mask','media','meme']);
  if (!ALLOWED_TYPES.has(payload?.type)) throw new Error('invalid type');
  // validate all required fields per type, reject extra keys
  const safe = Object.create(null); // no prototype inheritance

Null-guard the result:
  const tokens = await authStore.getTokens();
  if (!tokens?.accessToken) return false;
  return !authStore.isTokenExpired(cfg);

Invalidate the nonce immediately after successful authentication:
  // After line 224 (authenticated = true):
  this.currentNonce = null; // one-time use

Add explicit type guards before delegating to the service:
  if (typeof id !== 'string') throw new Error('invalid id');
  if (typeof enabled !== 'boolean') throw new Error('invalid enabled');

In the dev fast-path, skip saveTokens entirely and return after setting an in-memory only state, or use a flag to indicate the dev token should not be persisted:
  // Dev fast-path — do not persist to keytar
  return; // AuthStore.getTokens() will fall back to env var
